  "key": "value"
}
```

### Problem:

This only supports equality checks.

### You will eventually need:

* greater/less than
* existence checks
* multi-condition logic (AND/OR)

### Fix (minimal upgrade without overengineering):

Allow:

```json
requiresState: [
  {
    "key": "string",
    "op": "eq | neq | gt | lt | exists",
    "value": "any"
  }
]
```

You don’t need full boolean trees yet — just prevent early collapse.

