### 1. Core NodeType interface

This is the **runtime-facing contract** every node type must implement, backed by the Type Contract Layer:

```ts
export interface NodeType {
  /** Structural + typeData validation (pure, no side effects) */
  validate(node: NodeV5, hunt: HuntV5): {
    errors: string[];
    warnings: string[];
  };

  /** Normalization into a safe, fully-populated node */
  normalize(node: NodeV5, hunt: HuntV5): NodeV5;

  /** Called when the node becomes active */
  onEnter(node: NodeV5, ctx: NodeContext): void | Promise<void>;

  /** Called when the node is about to be left */
  onExit(node: NodeV5, ctx: NodeContext): void | Promise<void>;

  /** Pure render description (no direct DOM) */
  render(node: NodeV5, ctx: NodeContext): RenderModel;

  /** What this node depends on (items, assets, state keys, etc.) */
  getDependencies(node: NodeV5): NodeDependencies;

  /** Non-fatal issues that creators should know about */
  getWarnings(node: NodeV5, hunt: HuntV5): string[];
}
```

Where:

```ts
export interface NodeContext {
  state: GameState;          // key/value store
  inventory: InventoryState; // items
  time: TimeApi;             // timers
  nav: NavApi;               // goToNode, endHunt, etc.
  audio: AudioApi;           // sfx, music
  ui: UiApi;                 // overlays, toasts, modals
  log: LogApi;               // debug / analytics
}
```

`RenderModel` is a **pure description** (e.g. `{ type: 'story', title, body, choices }`) that the runtime renderer turns into actual DOM/UI.

